{"title":"45NRTH adds new Ragnarök Tall waterproof cycling boot, plus Wølfgar Winter Boot w/ dual BOA","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/26/45nrth-adds-new-ragnarok-tall-waterproof-cycling-boot-plus-wolfgar-winter-boot-w-dual-boa/","date":1635268280000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121829/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-feature.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"530\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121829/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-feature-800x530.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121829/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-feature-800x530.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121829/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-feature-297x197.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121829/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-feature-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121829/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-feature-768x509.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121829/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-feature-1536x1018.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121829/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-feature-2048x1357.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-276306\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Cyclocross is here, so you know what’s next—winter. Yup, soon it will be time to put away the bikes and dust off the trainers. Or not. Or some combination of both, it really doesn’t matter. What&nbsp;<em>does</em> matter is that if you’re planning on braving the elements, you should have the proper gear. And now one of the leading experts in winter cycling apparel has just announced two new boots that will keep you pedaling through shoulder season and deep winter.</p><h2>Ragnarök Tall</h2><div id=\"attachment_276332\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121331/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-12.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276332\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121331/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-12.jpg\" alt=\"Ragnarök Tall waterproof cycling boot\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1134\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121331/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-12.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121331/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-12-297x281.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121331/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-12-800x756.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121331/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-12-120x113.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121331/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-12-768x726.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p></div><p>Call it late Fall, early Spring, or just the shoulder or transition seasons, depending on where you live the new Ragnarök Tall could be a ride saver. Not a true winter shoe and definitely not a summer shoe, the Ragnarök Tall is for those cold, wet days where you need more protection than a shoe cover without something that will be <em>too</em> warm. 45NRTH suggests using these down to 25°f, though your use will vary on personal comfort, sock thickness, etc.</p><p>The obvious change here from the excellent Ragnarök is the addition of the much taller ankle cuff. That allows easy entry with a neoprene sleeve with velcro closure, but tall coverage to close the gap between your riding tights and shoes.</p><div id=\"attachment_276322\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121258/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-2.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276322\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121258/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-2.jpg\" alt=\"Ragnarök Tall waterproof cycling boot boa\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1326\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121258/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-2.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121258/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-2-271x300.jpg 271w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121258/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-2-800x884.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121258/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-2-109x120.jpg 109w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121258/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-2-768x849.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p></div><p>The floating “three-finger overlap” should allow the single Li2 Boa dial to better tighten the shoe over different foot shapes, especially when dirty. This was one of my main issues with the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/12/07/review-45nrth-ragnarok-boots-step-in-when-the-weather-starts-to-turn/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">previous Ragnarök,</a> so it’s nice to see it addressed.</p><div id=\"attachment_276323\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121301/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-3.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276323\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121301/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-3.jpg\" alt=\"Ragnarök Tall waterproof cycling boot lugs\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1233\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121301/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-3.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121301/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-3-292x300.jpg 292w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121301/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-3-800x822.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121301/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-3-117x120.jpg 117w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121301/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-3-768x789.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p></div><p>The outsole features a real rubber construction with anti-slip microglass filament lugs and a fiberglass-injected nylon midsole.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125320/45nrth-2022-Ragnarok-tall-boot-profile.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125320/45nrth-2022-Ragnarok-tall-boot-profile.jpg\" alt=\"Ragnarök Tall waterproof cycling boot profile\" width=\"1485\" height=\"1600\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125320/45nrth-2022-Ragnarok-tall-boot-profile.jpg 1485w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125320/45nrth-2022-Ragnarok-tall-boot-profile-278x300.jpg 278w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125320/45nrth-2022-Ragnarok-tall-boot-profile-800x862.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125320/45nrth-2022-Ragnarok-tall-boot-profile-111x120.jpg 111w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125320/45nrth-2022-Ragnarok-tall-boot-profile-768x827.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125320/45nrth-2022-Ragnarok-tall-boot-profile-1426x1536.jpg 1426w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1485px) 100vw, 1485px\"></a></p><p>The upper is constructed from “premium microfiber” and Tec Tuff toe and heel abrasion-resistant panels are added along with reflective hits and high visibility stripes. Offered in men’s 36-50 (no size 49) in full sizes only, the Ragnarök Tall will sell for $245.</p><h2>Wølfgar Deep Winter Cycling Boot</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121328/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-11.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121328/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-11.jpg\" alt=\"Wølfgar Deep Winter Cycling Boot\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1336\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121328/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-11.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121328/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-11-269x300.jpg 269w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121328/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-11-800x891.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121328/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-11-108x120.jpg 108w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121328/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-11-768x855.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Along similar lines, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/10/23/45nrth-wolvhammer-completely-redesigned-w-2-boots-in-1-wolfgar-winter-riding-boot-adds-boa/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">the previous Wølfgar</a> was an excellent deep winter boot. But one that included a single BOA dial to cinch down the entire bulky boot. New for 2022, the Wølfgar gets a welcome update including a dual-zone BOA system with chunky dials that look like they’d be great to use with thick gloves. That’s important considering the temperature range of the new Wølfgar is -25°F to 10°F. These certainly aren’t for all winter cyclists, but for those who really get out in the cold, these are probably the boots to get.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121322/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-9.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121322/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-9.jpg\" alt=\"Wølfgar Deep Winter Cycling Boot outsole\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1239\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121322/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-9.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121322/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-9-291x300.jpg 291w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121322/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-9-800x826.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121322/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-9-116x120.jpg 116w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26121322/45nrth-MY-2022-ragnarok-tall-wolfgar-fat-bike-winter-cycling-boots-9-768x793.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Using a “three-piece proprietary bottom assembly,” the Wølfgar has a rubber outsole with microglass lugs, and a two-bolt cleat pattern, though it includes a bolt-on plate that allows them to be used with flat pedals. <a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125327/45NRTH-Wolfgar-2022-winter-fat-biking-boots.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125327/45NRTH-Wolfgar-2022-winter-fat-biking-boots.jpg\" alt=\"Wølfgar Deep Winter Cycling Boot profile\" width=\"1641\" height=\"1600\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125327/45NRTH-Wolfgar-2022-winter-fat-biking-boots.jpg 1641w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125327/45NRTH-Wolfgar-2022-winter-fat-biking-boots-297x290.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125327/45NRTH-Wolfgar-2022-winter-fat-biking-boots-800x780.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125327/45NRTH-Wolfgar-2022-winter-fat-biking-boots-120x117.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125327/45NRTH-Wolfgar-2022-winter-fat-biking-boots-768x749.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26125327/45NRTH-Wolfgar-2022-winter-fat-biking-boots-1536x1498.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1641px) 100vw, 1641px\"></a></p><p>Inside, you’ll find a removable wool and faux fur boot liner, in addition to Aerogel lining on the footbed and above the toebox to keep in the heat and block out the cold. Gaiter hooks are offered for added protection in the harshest environments, and there’s a reflective panel on the back just in case your winter adventures take you on the pavement.</p><p>Offered in Men’s wide 36-50 (no 49) in full sizes only, the Wølfgar will sell for $495.</p><p><a href=\"https://45nrth.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>45nrth.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"2b4a4aebf3d06b7bbaf3b2c27eafff52560a4f7bb8dc2c5e42a09bf17583950b","category":"Cycling"}